          "text": "<div>concentration of 30% or more. When compressed, carbon dioxide is made into liquid which is stored in</div><div>steel cylinder. The ratio of the liter content of the cylinder to the quantity of carbon dioxide in kilogram is</div><div>called the “filling ratio\" and it is normally 0.67kg per litter.</div><div>1 千克二氧化碳將形成約 0.56 立方米的氣體，能够撲滅濃度為 30%或更高的火災。 壓縮時，二氧化碳被製成液體，</div><div>儲存在鋼瓶中。 氣瓶的升含量與二氧化碳量（千克）之比稱為“填充比”，通常為 0.67 千克每升。</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>資料來源Data Source：N6182_D2985010_F1</div><div><br></div>"
